/*Intuition :-
    Modular Arithmetic :-
    1) (a+b) % x = (a % x + b % x) % x ;
    2) (a*b) % x = ((a % x) * (b % x)) % x ;
    3) (a-b) % x = ((a % x) - (b % x) + x) % x ;
    4) (a/b) % x = (a % x) * ((1/b) % x ) % x ;
    Ekhane 1 / b holo b er multiplicative inverse . Er calculation korar jonno
    jei technique ta use hoy ta holo binary exponentiation, modular exponentiation .

    Modular Arithmetic er proyojon hoy karon , Onek shomoy kuno ekta problem er 
    answer calculation er shomoy answer onek boro hoye jay ja amader traditional
    variable {int , long , long long} e store kora jay nah . Tokhon amra oi answer
    ke int er range e rakhar jonno {998244353 , 1e9+7} type er prime number dara
    mod kori . Kuno songkha ke jei songkha diye mod kora hoy answer tar cheye 1 kom
    theke shuru kore 0 porjonto hote pare .

    Jei number ta diye mod kora hoy oi number ta prime choose korar karon holo prime
    number er modular multiplicative inverse nirnoy kora jay .
*/
